m><item><title>Not a true catholic</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/dC3PslN</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/dLaKelv.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/dC3PslN</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[Devi8tor]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Jack Prime must be found</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/JW19LG2</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/imU9pM5.png" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is not the greatest meme in the world, This is a tribute!</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/JW19LG2</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[ATLandNerdy]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Living my best life as a medieval peasant</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/pIbz78N</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/ACqWqAP.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I recently visited Evermore Park in Pleasant Grove, Utah. This is a permanent park that is a perfect blend of Renaissance Faire and Live Action Role Play</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/lyzWqqr.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Guests are encouraged to come in character and in costume! My name was Juniper. I just needed something to wear…</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/O89WLrW.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>I’ve always wanted to learn to sew and make costumes and used the pandemic to really dive in. Both corsets and skirts were handmade by me!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/jsgHxjr.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>The green was my first attempt and I’m so proud of it! Not perfect and my skills were definitely more refined by the navy one.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/GfvjVMU.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Evermore park also had a statue in their church graveyard of Saint Apollonia. The patron saint of teeth, which was so perfect for me because I’m a dental hygienist! See her forceps? Guests leave offerings to her for fortune and favor for good teeth.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/vPqa5Ax.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This park is beautiful. So much love is put into it by the actors. It’s also ridiculously affordable, I would have easily paid triple the price for admission. You interact with characters to go on quests to earn gold and other treasures. One wizard told our fortunes from Pokémon Cards!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/VhH0thV.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>These are some of my treasures I won in the park. A dragon’s tear from the dragon trainers guild, a special gold doubloon from the pirates, a ruby, a key to the inn so we would always have a place to stay if we came back to Evermore, a ring from the finger of a fairy, and I kept one of the pieces of gold which is just painted rocks. I gave the rest of my gold back to the Evermore actors to recycle to new guests.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/SRBvQnl.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>This is the Pigmyweed’s Inn, if you give the dwarf innkeeper Fergus 3 pieces of gold he will sing you a song. Since I visited the dragon trainers guild (which I joined) got a huge lifelike dragon! And they have baby dragons. There’s also jousts, archery, axe throwing, and more!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/7E96v8Z.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Stop in their attached restaurant and bar called Vander’s Keep. There I had some of the best venison of my life and amazing cocktails.</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/5oq0YVT.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>We were there on Fairy weekend when they had a lantern festival. You can choose to join the guild of fairies, pirates, knights, dragon trainers, and more!</div><div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/9iand2d.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>TLDR - Go LARP in Utah</div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/pIbz78N</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[faelurian]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>As an American I cannot blame them at all.</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/HE9q3Hw</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/umbOI6m.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/HE9q3Hw</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[rukeman]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>Bro, do you even Science?!</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/bGStyvQ</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/1T30Vqd.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/bGStyvQ</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[SteveSabbai]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>I carved all of this from Maple wood (trypophobia warning)</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/cjqTbK0</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/OU0elxe.gif" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div></div>]]></description><guid>https://imgur.com/a/cjqTbK0</guid><dc:creator><![CDATA[acadianmushrooms]]></dc:creator></item><item><title>WTF?</title><link>https://imgur.com/gallery/q21KPfI</link><description><![CDATA[<div><img alt="" src="https://i.imgur.com/kdr4H4I.jpg" style="max-width: 90%; height: auto;"></div><div><span></span></div><div>Tweet link.https://twitter.com/ChrisMurphyCT/status/1542254795779719169</div></div>]]></description>